name: ID 12
description:
Made from used vinyl record sleeves contributed by members of the public. A series of portraits, cut in half and rejoined with another to form a new face.

Hi-res image: 3000 x 3000 pixels

As a social art project, the process is open to everyone. Find out how to recycle and include your obsolete materials in future artworks by getting in touch.

The original painting was created in 2019.
